  "title": "Service Engineer (Lab & Scientific Instruments) #80333",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Laboratory Equipment Distributor</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Service Engineer</strong></li><li>Working Location: Marsiling</li><li>Working Hours: 5 Days, Monday – Friday (8.30am – 6pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Provide technical, engineering, and application support for Hitachi SEM systems and other assigned equipment.</li><li>Conduct routine and corrective servicing of scientific instruments to ensure optimal performance.</li><li>Handle equipment setup, installation, and commissioning processes.</li><li>Diagnose and resolve issues related to instruments, including PCB boards and electronic components.</li><li>Support and maintain failure analysis (FA) lab tools across both Malaysia and Singapore locations.</li><li>Advise customers on suitable spare parts during servicing and repair activities.</li><li>Responsibilities may evolve based on operational needs and management direction.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>At least Diploma in Chemistry, Biochemistry, or Electrical/ Electronic Engineering.</li><li>Minimum of 5-8 years of relevant industry experience.</li><li>Practical experience in operating and repairing scientific instruments, including PCB-level troubleshooting.</li><li>Ability to interpret and work with schematic diagrams.</li><li>Good team player with sharp analytical thinking and effective problem-solving abilities.</li><li>Familiarity with SEM/ EDX systems is an added advantage.</li><li>Willing to attend service calls and travel internationally when required.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#80333 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
